The paper proposes a framework for sorting elements that is algorithmically differentiable and applies it to various learning settings. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions applications to quantile regression and top-k accuracy, which are commonly studied in Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories, respectively. The paper also uses entropic regularization and Sinkhorn iterations, which are techniques commonly used in Neural Networks (cs.NE) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.NE, and cs.AI, in that order.
